Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo A 37-year-old man, Olufunsho Seriki, was on Monday arraigned before an Osun State Magistratesâ€™ Court sitting in Osogbo for stealing plumbing materials valued at N102,000. The accused was arraigned on two counts of house-breaking and stealing. Seriki allegedly broke into the shop of one Raphael Umezuriki and stole four PVC pipes valued at N12,000; a 1,000-litre water tank valued N48,000; and two 800-litre water tanks valued at N42,000. Seriki was said to have committed the offences on July 29, 2019, around 1pm at the Queens Academy, Ofatedo area of Osogbo. The offences, according to the police, are contrary to and punishable under Section 412 and 390 (9) of the Criminal Code, Cap 34 Vol. 2, Laws of Osun State, Nigeria, 2003. Represented by his counsel, Mr Okobe Najite, the accused pleaded not guilty when the charges were read to him. Magistrate Risikat Olayemi, while ruling on the bail application, admitted the accused to bail in the sum of N50,000 with one surety in like sum. She adjourned the case till October 31, 2019, for hearing. Copyright PUNCH.
